Katja and Claudia, both recovered from eating disorders, opened Germany's first restaurant for anorexics and bulimics.
The establishment provides a safe space for those sensitive about food, offering therapy and support.
Meanwhile, in Italy, children are bombarded with food ads on TV, contributing to the rise of eating disorders.
Researchers are exploring treatments like leptin and topiramate to help those struggling with binge eating.
Middle-aged women are also affected by anorexia and bulimia, facing unique challenges.
Despite the difficulties, recovery stories like Amanda's offer hope for those battling eating disorders.
